other_tests.findings: Normal Sertoli cell complement and germ cell maturation until the spermatocyte II stage. Sertoli and Leydig cells displayed positive inhibin H9251-subunit immunostaining. Only Leydig cells and spermatogonia stained positively for the inhibin H9252B-subunit.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Inhibin B and pan-H9251C-inhibin levels were high from clinical onset to adolescence, regardless of testosterone levels and gonadotropin suppression.
